expected_result: validate can apply the safe subset of fix-hint remediations automatically with preview support and per-fix reporting
actual_result: "Implemented --auto-fix/--dry-run/--fix-scope: derivable resolution and close_reason backfills applied through audited runUpdate; fixes.planned/applied/gated/failed_fixes rows carry item id, field, and equivalent pm command; full flag wiring across commander, contracts, MCP tables, completions, docs"
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-11T16:14:23.411Z",validate-autofix-agent,"DESIGN pm validate --auto-fix: (1) SAFE = deterministic + derivable + non-destructive. Implemented safe fixes: closed item missing resolution -> backfill from its own close_reason (else 'completed' default); closed item missing close_reason -> backfill from its existing resolution. expected/actual stay hint-only (no derivable source). Auto-fix NEVER closes/cancels/deletes items. (2) --dry-run previews; output has fixes.{planned,applied,gated,failed}_fixes[] where each row = item_id + check + field + equivalent pm command. (3) --fix-scope <scope> (repeatable or comma-separated; metadata|resolution|lifecycle) is an EXACT allowlist of what may be mutated; default grant = metadata+resolution; lifecycle must be named explicitly (pm-8jss). (4) --auto-fix with no --check-* flags runs only the fix-capable checks (metadata, resolution, lifecycle). (5) Fixes are applied through the normal audited runUpdate/runFiles/runDocs command paths (lazy-imported so read-only validate stays light); per-fix failures land in failed_fixes[] and never abort the run. Checks in the output always reflect the PRE-fix state. Plan logic is pure in src/core/validate/fix-planning.ts."
close_reason: "Shipped pm validate --auto-fix with --dry-run, --fix-scope allowlist, and fixes output surface"
body: ""
